The United States strongly condemns the recent attacks on the people of Syria in Eastern Ghouta by Russia and the Assad regime. They offer condolences to the families affected and call on the international community to condemn these attacks. The destruction of medical facilities and the use of siege tactics in Eastern Ghouta are particularly troubling. The United States supports the United Nations' call for a cessation of violence to allow for the delivery of humanitarian supplies and medical evacuations. They also urge Russia and its partners to fulfill their obligations regarding de-escalation zones and to end further attacks against civilians in Syria. The article emphasizes the need for a political resolution for Syria that respects the will of the Syrian people, in line with UN Security Council Resolution 2254 and the November 2017 Da Nang Joint Statement between President Donald J. Trump and Russian President Vladimir Putin.